   "source": [
    "### Method 2: Parametric (Variance-Covariance) VaR\n",
    "\n",
    "- Assumes returns are **normally distributed**\n",
    "- Uses the mean and standard deviation to compute VaR analytically\n",
    "- $$\\text{VaR}_{\\alpha} = \\mu + z_{\\alpha} \\cdot \\sigma$$\n",
    "- where $z_{\\alpha}$ is the z-score at confidence level $\\alpha$\n",
    "- ✅ Fast, easy to compute, good for linear portfolios\n",
    "- ❌ Underestimates risk if returns have fat tails (which they usually do!)\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "c085dda2",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
